\f0\fs56 \cf2 Pickled Hot Cherry Peppers\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\ql\qnatural

\fs54 \cf0 Ingredients\

\fs46 Makes enough for 4 servings\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}20 hot cherry peppers\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons olive oil\
{\listtext	\'95	}5 cups Champagne or white-wine vinegar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup coarse salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 tablespoons sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cloves garlic, crushed\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon whole black peppercorns\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 sprigs fresh thyme\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 dried bay leaf\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\ql\qnatural

\fs54 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs42 \cf3 {\listtext	1.	}Preheat oven to 500 degrees.
\f1\b\fs44 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs42 {\listtext	2.	}Using a sharp knife, split peppers lengthwise, but do not cut all the way through peppers, leaving them whole. Place in a large bowl and drizzle with olive oil; toss to combine. Transfer to a baking sheet and roast until slightly softened, about 10 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl; set aside.
\f1\b\fs44 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs42 {\listtext	3.	}Combine vinegar, 1 cup water, salt, sugar, garlic, peppercorns, thyme, and bay leaf in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Pour vinegar mixture over roasted peppers and let stand at room temperature until cool. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 days and up to 4 months before using. Bring to room temperature before eating.
\f1\b\fs44 \
